slender and delicate.

00:00:50.033 --> 00:00:51.501 position:35% line:89% align:start
By design!

00:00:51.634 --> 00:00:53.834 position:7% line:83% align:start
Repetitive tasks like whipping
eggs result in something

00:00:53.968 --> 00:00:56.067 position:19% line:89% align:start
special known as STMF!

00:00:56.200 --> 00:00:58.400 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[clucking]
-"Some thin, meek fowl"?

00:00:58.534 --> 00:01:01.334 position:13% line:83% align:start
It stands for "slow-twitch
muscle fibers."

00:01:01.467 --> 00:01:03.868 position:13% line:83% align:start
By intentionally subjecting
my arms to such prolonged,

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.667 position:7% line:83% align:start
low-burden exercise, I develop
lithe yet firm arms

00:01:06.801 --> 00:01:08.434 position:21% line:83% align:start
that aren't hampered
by bulging muscles,

00:01:08.567 --> 00:01:10.501 position:24% line:83% align:start
no offense intended
to present company.

00:01:10.634 --> 00:01:12.467 position:35% line:83% align:start
-Oh... Hm?
-But there's more!

00:01:12.601 --> 00:01:14.167 position:30% line:83% align:start
One of the most
critical factors in muscle

00:01:14.300 --> 00:01:16.400 position:21% line:89% align:start
development is diet.

00:01:16.534 --> 00:01:17.934 position:27% line:89% align:start
Ah... [chomping]

00:01:18.067 --> 00:01:20.701 position:13% line:83% align:start
The majority of my calories
in sweets come from complex

00:01:20.834 --> 00:01:22.200 position:10% line:89% align:start
carbohydrates and tasty fats.

00:01:22.334 --> 00:01:24.667 position:21% line:83% align:start
They all have little
to no protein to speak of.

00:01:24.801 --> 00:01:26.334 position:35% line:83% align:start
My muscles
don't stand a chance.

00:01:26.467 --> 00:01:28.934 position:24% line:83% align:start
I order you to eat
real food from now on!

00:01:29.067 --> 00:01:30.267 position:33% line:83% align:start
-[Pas groans]
-Got it?

